The paper deals with 3D face recognition, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of feature extraction algorithms and genetic algorithms for feature selection suggests that the paper may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of depth maps and spherical patches suggests that the paper may also fall under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
